    "language": "en",
    "md5": "1c7c4bdfc5cc1c3e4b629d530435fe88",
    "chunk_size_bytes": 1976,
    "chunk_text": "\u201cAnd Lord Greene MR\u2026treated bad faith as interchangeable with unreasonableness and extraneous considerations. Bad faith therefore scarcely has an independent existence as a distinct ground of invalidity.\u201d [emphasis added]. 30. Accordingly, on the one hand, the 98 petitioners who had a legitimate\n\nexpectation of being recruited has been denied and their expectations\n\nviolated. Similarly, the decision to change the policy by Circular No.\n\nevent, is unreasonable vis-\u00e0-vis the said 98 petitioners, as it appears\n\nthat the same was for an extraneous consideration and made in bad\n\nfaith, to that extent. Even if this does not necessarily imply any moral\n\nturpitude, such exercise of power is mala fide as a matter of law.\n\nConclusion.\n\n31. Accordingly, I hold that the 98 petitioners hereinafter mentioned are\n\nentitled to the relief as follows, in respect of prayer (d). A writ of\n\nmandamus is accordingly issued directing the respondent 5A, the\n\nDirector General of the Department of Archaeology, to appoint the 1st,\n\n18th, 21st, 43rd, 49th, 50th, 58th, 60th, 61st, 63rd, 65th, 66th, 79th,\n\n80th, 81st, 84th, 91st, 94th, 99th, 104th, 107th, 120th, 121st, 125th,\n\n126th, 127th, 133rd, 142nd, 148th, 151st, 152nd, 155th, 156th, 157th,\n\n158th, 160th, 169th, 171st, 175th, 180th, 183rd, 188th, 194th, 196th,\n\n199th, 200th, 208th, 209th, 215th, 216th, 217th, 218th, 220th, 227th,\n\n231st, 233rd, 235th, 247th, 251st, 253rd, 256th, 258th, 261st, 267th,\n\nWRT/0127/20\n\nPage 55 of 56\n\n269th, 273rd, 279th, 285th, 286th, 290th, 292nd, 294th, 295th, 296th,\n\n302nd, 306th, 315th, 316th, 317th, 322nd, 323rd, 336th, 337th, 341st,\n\n342nd, 344th, 345th, 347th, 348th, 350th, 353rd, 354th, 356th, 364th,\n\n366th, 384th, 386th, and 390th petitioners to the respective posts such\n\npetitioner has been successful at the interviews as depicted in X-1 and\n\nX-2. The said appointments are to be made with effect from a date\n\npreceding the date on which appointments were made to these posts,"
